  "messages": [
    {
      "id": 721,
      "from_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "to_id": "cec50b17:23",
      "content": "Extract the inline CSS and JS from `public/index.html` into separate files `public/style.css` and `public/app.js`. The dashboard is served by `express.static('public')` so no server changes are needed — just link the files from HTML.\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Extract everything between `<style>` and `</style>` (there is one large style block) into `public/style.css`. Replace the `<style>...</style>` block in `index.html` with `<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"style.css\">`.\n\n2. Extract everything between `<script>` and `</script>` (the large inline script near the bottom) into `public/app.js`. Replace the `<script>...</script>` block in `index.html` with `<script src=\"app.js\"></script>` (keep it at the same position in the document, before `</body>`).\n\n3. No bundler, no minification — plain files. No other changes to logic or content.\n\n4. Verify: `grep -c '<style>' public/index.html` should return 0, `grep -c '<script>' public/index.html` should return 1 (just the src tag).\n\n5. Commit all three files (`index.html`, `style.css`, `app.js`) with message: `Extract inline CSS and JS to public/style.css and public/app.js`\n\nReport DONE to cec50b17:0.",
      "priority": 5,
      "created_at": 1780734663644,
      "read_at": 1780734667155,
